{"kind":"project","sections":[{"title":"Use your first OUDS components","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"hero","chapter":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","image":"ic_component_intro.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30,"backgroundImage":"ic_component_intro.png"},{"tasks":[{"title":"Add basic components","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, prepare the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContentView"},{"type":"text","text":" by adding inside it a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollView"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"caption":[],"code":"tutorial-3-1.swift","runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, let’s add radio buttons to let the user choose its gender."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The official components are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadio"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadioItem"},{"type":"text","text":", but the package has also a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadioPicker"},{"type":"text","text":" to implement quicky a group of radios."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This component can be replaced by your own."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The radio picker is defined by an array of values to display radio items associated to a tag, i.e. an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" thing shared through a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inside a picker the user can select only one value, not zero."}]}],"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add such picker with three items inside.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-3-2.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-2.png","type":"step"},{"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-3.png","code":"tutorial-3-3.swift","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a checkbox item with only two states."}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The radio picker is alone, it is the time to add below a checkbox. OUDS provides two components: "},{"code":"OUDSCheckbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which is a simple checkbox, and "},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which is a checkbox (duh!) with additional texts and icons."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The state of the checkbox is shared through a boolean "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"State"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In some cases you may need to use "},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},{"text":" if you want a three-states checkbox.","type":"text"}]}]},{"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-4.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are also components who do not have any behaviors and are here only for visual rendering, for example dividers which can be horizontal or vertical."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A divider is, in the end, a stroke with a color. You will see later, colors in OUDS have two values: a light mode value, and a dark mode value. Here the divider can have a color which can change, or not."}]}],"media":null,"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Choose to add an instance of ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"code":"tutorial-3-4.swift","type":"step"},{"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-5.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With radio and checkbox, OUDS provides also switch elements (toggles). They can be alone ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitch"},{"type":"text","text":") or with texts ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Just like the checkbox, the switch exposes its state through a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a switch item, it will be used as a trick to force the change of the color scheme for the view for our future operations.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You will then be able to see the automatic changes of colors when you switch the color scheme.","type":"text"}]}],"code":"tutorial-3-5.swift","type":"step"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users may need to navigate outside the app, like, for example, opening a website. Thus the "},{"code":"OUDSLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component can be integrated. It can be only with a text or also a chevron indicator."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-6.png","media":null,"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the app and make it open the iOS documentation OUDS website.","type":"text"}]}],"code":"tutorial-3-6.swift"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s add a button with some rules: if checkbox is not checked it is disabled. When tapped, change the style of the button during 5 seconds.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the end, we can also add a button. Button are one of the most used components in an app and bring a lof of the power and the style of the brand."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can find it with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Such button has an appearance changing its colors, and also a style (loading or not).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thanks to the theme, the enabled, disabled, hover, focus or pressed states are managed.","type":"text"}]}],"code":"tutorial-3-7.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-7.png","type":"step"}],"contentSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We will work on a kind of formular using main OUDS components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Feel free to style and design things as you want.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"anchor":"Add-basic-components"}],"kind":"tasks"},{"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"choices":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No! The components use the design specifications, i.e. tokens, thanks to the theme, to define the style they must have in all cases."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the reason why the "},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is so important: it injects the theme as environment variable so that any component can get it to define its style."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does the developer using OUDS component need to manage the look and feel of the components?"}]}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[]}]},{"title":"Add more OUDS components","featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","action":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"overridingTitle":"Get started"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Components can be similar to iOS native components, or can also be original and strongly related to Orange Unified Design System needs."}],"kind":"callToAction"}],"metadata":{"role":"project","title":"Use your first OUDS components","category":"Orange Unified Design System","categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents","modules":[{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Preparation-of-the-theme"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Add-basic-components"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Richer-and-more-original-components-of-OUDS","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Add-basic-components","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}]},{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Use-of-tokens","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Use-of-view-modifiers","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Final-result","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Typography,-view-modifiers-and-tokens"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Go-further-with-more-ressources","projects":[{"sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further#More-resources"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further"}]}],"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/$volume","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Check Your Understanding","type":"text"}],"title":"Check Your Understanding"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-5-styling-things":{"role":"project","title":"Styling things","type":"topic","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things","estimatedTime":"30min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Even if components increase the identity of your apps, it is not enough. Typography, fonts and tokens are here to improve that."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-5-styling-things"},"tutorial-3-7.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"tutorial-3-7.png","alt":"A radio picker, an horizontal divider, a checkbox item, a switch item, a link and a button","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-7.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"tutorial-3-4.png":{"identifier":"tutorial-3-4.png","alt":"A radio picker, an horizontal divider and a checkbox item","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-4.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents/Preparation-of-the-theme":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Preparation-of-the-theme","role":"article","abstract":[],"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents\/preparation-of-the-theme","title":"Preparation of the theme"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS":{"role":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[],"title":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents\/use-of-first-components-provided-by-ouds","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding":{"title":"Check Your Understanding","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check Your Understanding"}],"type":"link","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies":{"role":"project","title":"Swift Package integration","type":"topic","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies"},"tutorial-3-7.swift":{"content":["\/\/","\/\/ Software Name: OUDS iOS","\/\/ SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright (c) Orange SA","\/\/ SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT","\/\/","\/\/ This software is distributed under the MIT license,","\/\/ the text of which is available at https:\/\/opensource.org\/license\/MIT\/","\/\/ or see the \"LICENSE\" file for more details.","\/\/","\/\/ Authors: See CONTRIBUTORS.txt","\/\/ Software description: A SwiftUI components library with code examples for Orange Unified Design System","\/\/","","import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","struct ContentView: View {","","    @State var selectedGender: Genders = .male","    @State var termsAccepted: Bool = false","    @State var switchToDarkMode: Bool = false","    @State var creatingProfile: Bool = false","","    @Environment(\\.openURL) var openUrl","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selectedGender,","                            radios: genderRadioValues(),","                            placement: .horizontal(false))","","            OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","","            OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $termsAccepted, label: \"I accept the terms of use\")","","            OUDSSwitchItem(\"Switch to dark mode\", isOn: $switchToDarkMode)","","            OUDSLink(text: \"Go to the website\", indicator: .next) {","                openUrl.callAsFunction(URL(string: \"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\")!)","            }","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Create my profile\",","                       appearance: .strong,","                       style: creatingProfile ? .loading : .default)","            {","                creatingProfile = true","                DispatchQueue.main.asyncAfter(deadline: .now() + 5) {","                    creatingProfile = false","                }","            }.disabled(!termsAccepted)","        }.preferredColorScheme(switchToDarkMode ? .dark : .light)","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Utils","","    enum Genders: String, Hashable {","        case male","        case female","        case nonBinary","    }","","    func genderRadioValues() -> [OUDSRadioPickerData<Genders>] {","        [","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.male, label: \"Mr\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.female, label: \"Ms\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.nonBinary, label: \"Other\"),","        ]","    }","}"],"type":"file","identifier":"tutorial-3-7.swift","fileName":"Content.swift","fileType":"swift","syntax":"swift","highlights":[{"line":22},{"line":41},{"line":42},{"line":43},{"line":44},{"line":45},{"line":46},{"line":47},{"line":48},{"line":49},{"line":50}]},"ic_component_intro.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSThemesContract\/ic_component_intro.png"}],"alt":"OUDS components logo","identifier":"ic_component_intro.png"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries":{"kind":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","role":"pseudoSymbol","abstract":[{"text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework.","type":"text"}],"type":"section","title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-6-going-further#More-resources":{"role":"pseudoSymbol","type":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Since you have learnt how OUDS works with theme, themeable view, components, tuning and vieww modifiers, it is time now to discover some online resources."}],"title":"More resources","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-6-going-further#More-resources","kind":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further#More-resources"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app":{"role":"pseudoSymbol","type":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything."}],"title":"Basic structure for the app","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","kind":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding":{"title":"Check Your Understanding","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check Your Understanding"}],"type":"link","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding","title":"Check Your Understanding","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check Your Understanding"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding"},"tutorial-3-6.png":{"identifier":"tutorial-3-6.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-6.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"A radio picker, an horizontal divider, a checkbox item, a switch item and a link","type":"image"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-6-going-further":{"title":"Going further with more resources","kind":"project","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"10min","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-6-going-further","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Since you have learnt how OUDS works with theme, themeable view, components, tuning and vieww modifiers, it is time now to discover some online resources."}]},"tutorial-3-3.swift":{"content":["\/\/","\/\/ Software Name: OUDS iOS","\/\/ SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright (c) Orange SA","\/\/ SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT","\/\/","\/\/ This software is distributed under the MIT license,","\/\/ the text of which is available at https:\/\/opensource.org\/license\/MIT\/","\/\/ or see the \"LICENSE\" file for more details.","\/\/","\/\/ Authors: See CONTRIBUTORS.txt","\/\/ Software description: A SwiftUI components library with code examples for Orange Unified Design System","\/\/","","import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","struct ContentView: View {","","    @State var selectedGender: Genders = .male","    @State var termsAccepted: Bool = false","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selectedGender,","                            radios: genderRadioValues(),","                            placement: .horizontal(false))","","            OUDSCheckboxItem(isOn: $termsAccepted, label: \"I accept the terms of use\")","        }","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Utils","","    enum Genders: String, Hashable {","        case male","       